  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "TCCC is often introduced as a set of clinical priorities, but its deeper contribution is decision structure: it makes explicit that the tactical situation is part of the clinical problem.\nIn hospital medicine, the environment is engineered to support care. In TCCC, care must be engineered to fit the environment.\n¶Tactics drive medicine The phrase \u0026ldquo;tactics drive medicine\u0026rdquo; is shorthand for a systems constraint: the team cannot provide care that would predictably create additional casualties, compromise mission-essential actions, or prevent movement to a safer position where more care becomes possible.\n",
  "keywords": "military-medicine, trauma, emergency-medicine",
  "name": "Decision-Making Under Constraint",
